column1: To say a little about myself, I(rajeshcmehta) am a senior media professional having worked in some of the biggest ad companies since last 22 years at a very senior level. Born and brought up in Bombay. Currently I live with my younger daughter (age 12 years) She has got admission in an international boarding school at Gujarat from june 2011, My elder daughter is (age 20) is studying in Pune and staying in a hostel in Pune. I give family values high priority in life, something that I will never give up. I believe in living life to the fullest and I take life as it comes. I am a very religious person. Have immense faith in God and though I have had a very bad marriage which I pulled for 21 years. I would like to depict my views regarding marriage you must have heard people saying that we were married because we were in love but according to me it is the other way round... love is a result of good marriage. Of course it requires some ingredients to hold this notion true... these ingredients are whether both partners share the same goal about life whether they could communicate in every manner the fear/hesitance, his/her behavior in general and also whether you are ready to accept the person she/he is with no wild assumptions, no compromise, and no overlooking or underlooking of facts. I believe in accepting the person as he or she is than force myself to believe that, that person would change afterwards in extremes. If anyone of them is missing then the integrity of marriage is missing. Once these conditions are fulfilled to an acceptable level then marriage is nothing but a pleasurable journey!!! . My family was in Building Construction business my mother is a home maker. My father is retired. My brother has his own business. My sister is married and settled in Ahmedabad. Currently i am staying with my younger daughter in mumbai. I am born & based in Mumbai. Though I have been living here for more than 20 years. I am always high on life, and strive to ensure thereAa?a?s never a dull moment. The fragrance of rain drenching the parched earth, the flash of lightning against an ink-blue sky, the temple bells chiming on festival day... itAa?a?s these small pleasures in life that make me happy. I respect all religions and faiths. When I am passing by a church, gurudwara or masjid, my hands immediately fold into a Namaste as a mark of reverence. For me all religions are the same and lead to almighty. ItAa?a?s just that each one professes it in a different way. My Education:Diploma in Marketing & Sales Management, from Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies (Mumbai,India). ADMANAa?A s Diploma Course in Advertising Management conducted by Indian Society of Advertisers (ISA) Winner of ISA Adman Trophy (Mumbai,India). B.COM Aa?a?? University Of Mumbai (Commerce) from Mithibai College.(Mumbai,India) Advanced Online Advertising Program at NIIT IMPERIA & Google (Mumbai,India) I am currently a free member.u can connect with me on FB also,"My Ideal woman is a nice mix of grounded Indian and growing western customs. One who will communicate to me in all matters; good, bad or indifferent and health & fitness is an important part of her life. A presentable woman with a romantic soul and zest for life's adventures; grateful for the good ones, strong enough to endure the not so good and able to learn & grow together to ensure there are more good than bad. I know above are a lot of things that sound so perfect... . For a relationship to be successful, it must be based on mutual understanding. column1:
Outlook & Personality

I am a strong, independent, self confident and self motivated person. I love to travel, read, learn new things and I also enjoy quiet times to meditate and contemplate. I enjoy quiet long walks, hiking, swimming and exercising regularly as well as the simple pleasures of life like that nature provides eg a nice sunset etc. I love sports and hobbies and am involved in a number of them that include aero-modeling, scuba-diving, skiing, cricket, etc. 
I believe that I have a good mix of eastern and western values. While I am well educated (2 Masters degrees & a CA designation), I am driven by a strong value system where money & status etc mean less to me than sound character and human values. 

Family

I come from a family of professionals. My father (late) was a civil engineer. My brother is a lawyer, is married and has a son and currently lives with my mother (retired teacher) in Bombay. We are a God-fearing family progressive family that has a good mix of eastern and western values.,"I am looking for someone who can share these simple things with, someone that I can love and respect and that will reciprocate the same.
I am looking for a reasonably balanced person whose personality is based in sound values, a companion who will be a good / best friend first and my wife only thereafter.
If you that person please write to me, I would love to hear from you.",,,29 Dec 1963,09:54:00,Canada,Mumbai,Athletic,,,Gujarati,,,,Wheatish ,,Self,MBA/PGDM,"49 yrs, 5ft 5in,

column1:
I describe myself as a simple and decent man who is emotional in nature. Further, my personality reflects my hard working nature and true devotion towards my work.
In my professional life I am a very serious person and do my work with complete devotion. Presently I am working as a Deputy General Manager. In future I would like to continue with my profession in the same field and reach the top position in life.
I am a straight forward person and speak freely. I dona??t hesitate in saying anything. Sometimes my straight forward nature gets negative for me but I feel proud as I dona??t talk behind anyonea??s back.
I give due respect to my family and my parents. My mother is a homemaker and father has retired from his profession. 
In my school I was a bright student of my class and have received various appreciations from my teachers. In my higher education sector I have completed B tech from Roorkee University. 
I have very few friends in my life and they are my real support. Further, I like to spend most of my time with them watching TV and travelling to new destinations. I love to listen to some of my favorite tracks as it relaxes me and gives me time for myself.,"The girl, with whom I will get married to, should be a simple female with calm and patient nature. She must be homely and must respect the family values we follow.

I am looking for a non working woman to enter my life who can understand me and bring the best out of me. She should be well settled in her life and must be from a decent family background. She should be well educated and I would prefer a girl from North India region.

Being a mature person I am aware of the responsibilities at home. Therefore I am ready to share those responsibilities with my wife. This way she will also feel at ease and will also feel support from my side. I will be always there for her and will always support her. I am ready to spend my life with her if she is like the one I am looking for.
,,,23 Aug 1964,,India,,,,,Agarwal,,,,,,Son,BE B.Tech (Engineering),49 yrs, 5ft 6in,

column1: Well, what can one say about oneself without it sounding like a sales pitch but here goes....... column1: Life brings so many up and downs, that you go thru life wondering if and when that someone will come into your life. If you give up hope - than you have lost. I believe that there is some ONE for everyone that is meant to be theirs. I believe that everything that you experience or go thru is what makes you who you are. I have own a business in Mumbai and now started new venture in Exports. Have mainly travelled to UK & Europe. I am a Caring, Loving, Affectionate, Sincere and Committed Indian Gujarati Brahmin guy with a good sense of humour and am fun loving. Although i am a mix of both the cultures east & west, i do have value & respect for indian traditions, culture & am proud to be an indian. I also enjoy leisure past times such as reading, music,swimming, computers, traveling, explore new possibilties life has to offer. I love to listen soft music when in a good mood. I am a nature lover and love to go on long walks, specially on a beach and love to roam along with nature. I love rain, greenery, etc ..... I am looking for a life partner.. who is educated, senstive, down to earth ,trustworthy, with a sense of humour. I believe all relationships are build on respect, trust and affection which comes from understanding and patience. I am looking for a decent,loving and caring person. should be understanding, a good companion to laugh with & share a meaningful life with.should be able to support my ideas & share my dreams. Who can be a friend for me for life. Someone i can trust, appreciate and lead life to the maximum. You should be sincere and looking to commit with the right person. Thanks for your time and good luck with your search.,,,29 to 40,10 May 1964,,India,,Athletic,Doesn't Matter,,Brahmin - Audichya,Brahmin,,,Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,Other Post Graduation,"49 yrs, 5ft 11in,
